# Home Nerwork Topology

## Project Objective
To discover, identify and visually document all active devices on your local home network. 
You will detemine the networks IP range, find live hosts and identify what are those devices.

## What you will need
  - Your Home Network
  - Command Line Interace: Command Prompt for Windows and Terminal for MacOS and Linux
  - A Network Scanner: nmap or zenmap(preferred)

## Follow the Sequence
Phase 1: Detemine your scope
         - Open your Terminal
         - Use Command: ipconfig for Windows or ifconfig for Linux
         - You will see a bunch of newtorks in the CLI Interface
         - Identify your computer's local IP address, the Subnet Mask, and the Default Gateway (your router)
         - This shows that the range of IP Address of your network
           e.g:  inet 10.116.73.163  netmask 255.255.255.0  broadcast 10.116.73.255

Phase 2: Active Scanning
         - Run your choosen network scanner against your network range
         - ping every ip address and get response back
         - use command: traceroute this will icmp protocol determine the router

Phase 3: Device Identification
         - Use Wireshark and Zenmap to map the devices and identify the type of devices usinf its IP Address and MAC Address

Phase 4: Diagam
        - Draw a diagram of your home network or use cisco packer tracer
